{"parse":{"title":"Nalapanima","pageid":25842307,"revid":860168969,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Nalapanima</b> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Musical_play\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Musical play\">musical play</a> (Geeti Natak)<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> describing patriotism of a Nepalese soldier during <a href=\"/wiki/Anglo-Nepalese_War\" title=\"Anglo-Nepalese War\">Anglo-Nepalese War</a> at the <a href=\"/wiki/Battle_of_Nalapani\" title=\"Battle of Nalapani\">Battle of Nalapani</a> in 1814 AD,<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> fought under the command of <a href=\"/wiki/Balbhadra_Kunwar\" title=\"Balbhadra Kunwar\">Balbhadra Kunwar</a>. A wounded Nepalese soldier sought help from the British camp. He was grateful for the humaniterian help from the British but defied an offer to join British army (<a href=\"/wiki/Gurkha_War\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gurkha War\">Gurkha War</a>). \n</p><p>The Drama was staged at the Rastriya Nachghar (<a href=\"/wiki/Nepal\" title=\"Nepal\">Nepal</a>). Lyrics were written by Bala Krishna \u2018Sama\u2019 and music composed by <a href=\"/wiki/Shiva_Shankar\" title=\"Shiva Shankar\">Shiva Shankar</a>. After few years the drama was re-edited by Deepak Jangam and staged again. The songs of the album comprise distinctive blending of Nepalese folk styles and modern light touch.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The album also contains some unique duet songs sung by <a href=\"/wiki/Narayan_Gopal\" title=\"Narayan Gopal\">Narayan Gopal</a> and his mentor Manik Ratna.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Songs\">Songs</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Nalapanima&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Songs\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ol><li>Piyo..., piyo:   (<a href=\"/wiki/Narayan_Gopal\" title=\"Narayan Gopal\">Narayan Gopal</a> and Manik Ratna)</li>\n<li>Ke har khai Ayewu:  (<a href=\"/wiki/Shiva_Shankar\" title=\"Shiva Shankar\">Shiva Shankar</a> and Narayan Gopal)</li>\n<li>Chora naro: (Kamala Shrestha)</li>\n<li>Haye mero pritam: (Kamala Shrestha)</li>\n<li>Awu awau relimai: (Manik Ratna)</li>\n<li>Ama timilai: (Narayan Gopal)</li>\n<li>Chomoluma shikhara:  (Shiva Shankar and Kamala Shrestha)</li>\n<li>Agalagi nibhawunu paryo: (Manik Ratna)</li>\n<li>Aye.. Ayen: (Manik Ratna)</li>\n<li>Najawu murkha bhai: (Narayan Gopal)</li>\n<li>Jana dewu aba: (Manik Ratna)</li>\n<li>Huncha huncha: (Narayan Gopal and Manik Ratna)</li></ol>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Nalapanima&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.shivashankar.org\">http://www.shivashankar.org</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.nepalarmy.mil.np/history1.php\">http://www.nepalarmy.mil.np/history1.php</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.murchunga.net/Shiva_Shankar_Nalapanima/\">http://www.murchunga.net/Shiva_Shankar_Nalapanima/</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.ekantipur.com/nepal/article/?id=1481\">http://www.ekantipur.com/nepal/article/?id=1481</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2177\nCached time: 20180918195507\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.028 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.038 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 120/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 314/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 74/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 1483/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.003/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 525 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   23.675      1 Template:Reflist\n100.00%   23.675      1 -total\n 15.37%    3.640      1 Template:Main_other\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:25842307-0!canonical and timestamp 20180918195507 and revision id 860168969\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","*":"Musicals_inspired_by_real-life_events"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Works_about_wars"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Nepal_in_fiction"}],"links":[{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Anglo-Nepalese War"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Balbhadra Kunwar"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Battle of Nalapani"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Gurkha War"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Musical play"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Narayan Gopal"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Nepal"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Shiva Shankar"}],"templates":[{"ns":10,"exists":"","*":"Template:Reflist"},{"ns":10,"exists":